Pentair Ltd. (PNR) , a water filtration
company, said today that shareholders approved an almost 9
percent dividend increase.  Quarterly dividends will rise to 25 cents a share from 23
cents and be paid for the third and fourth quarters of this year
and the first two quarters on 2014, the company said in a
statement. The stock has gained almost 27 percent the past year.  The company, which merged last year with Tyco International
Ltd.â€™s flow-control busines, is incorporated in Switzerland for
